**Step 5 — Claude Sonnet 4.6 Thinking — How to Use it Wisely:**

This is the expensive model. Here is exactly when to use it and when not to.

---

**Use Claude Sonnet 4.6 Thinking for:**

| Task | Why |
|---|---|
| Building entire new modules from scratch | Complex multi-file architecture |
| Hard debugging across 5+ files | Needs deep reasoning |
| Database schema design | Critical decisions |
| Complex business logic | WAC, GST, payout calculations |
| Flutter app architecture | New territory |

---

**Do NOT use Thinking for:**

| Task | Use Instead |
|---|---|
| Fixing a small bug in one file | Claude Sonnet 4.6 without thinking |
| Adding a field to a form | Regular Sonnet |
| Writing a repository function | Regular Sonnet |
| CSS and UI fixes | Regular Sonnet or Haiku |
| Writing test cases | Regular Sonnet |
| Updating documentation | Haiku |

Thinking mode costs roughly 3x to 5x more tokens than regular Sonnet. Use it deliberately not by default.

